Happy Full Moon in Gemini! The moon shines bright all throughout the week, and under the Gemini influence this moon will help to open the mind’s eye to new ideas, interests, opportunities, communications, logistics, and also offer clarity and closure.

The planet of action and aggression, Mars, is also retrograde in the sign of Gemini. When Mars is stationed retrograde, it brings up an internal revision process regarding work and action. Perhaps the wheels have been turning in your mind about how you make decisions, how you spend your time working, how you go about your work, or what you are looking to get out of your vocation. 

With the Moon and Mars in Gemini, this pulls focus on the Gemini themes of communication, curiosity, clarity, and social connection, BUT with Mars retrograde there could be some irritation or angst coming through. 

Use the full moon to see what comes up regarding your ways of communicating, your collaborations, and your connections. If there is something you have been searching for answers on, let this full moon guide you towards clarity. If there is something you’ve been trying to let go of, now is the time you can release your grip and move in a completely new direction with Mars Rx in Gemini. 

Jupiter, the planet of luck, abundance and expansion, is in its ruling sign of Pisces until the end of the year - serving fortune, spiritual abundance, and all around blessings. Trust that if there is something that you’ve been meaning to let go of, Jupiter in Pisces will help you to let go and level up. 

If you’re looking for connection or curious about someone, now is the time to take action and communicate! Jupiter in Pisces helps us to restore optimism into our lives and connect with something deeper in order to heal the mental and emotional body. Sit with what comes up, and find a spiritual outlet to connect and transcend!♊️

#fullmooningemini #fullcoldmoon #marsretrograce #jupiterinpisces

Today marks the shortest day of the year, the day we honor the shadows and turn inward to reflect on the light within.🕯️

Take some time to reflect on what strengthens your light, what qualities you possess that keep that flame burning, what experiences or virtues that fuel your fire, what friends or loved ones contribute to your inner  radiance and help you shine. This is Mother Nature’s New Year, our chance to reflect on the year and honor our connection to the light amidst the darkness.🕯️

Carve out a bit of extra time to journal, meditate and cultivate your inner landscape during these potent days of reflection around the Solstice and the upcoming new moon in Capricorn. Listen to your inner visions and dreams. Tend to the flames of the heart within and let them light your way forward!✨

⁣
The 4 Journaling Prompts Are:⁣
⁣
HOME | In this area of my life I want…⁣

MIND | In this area of my life I want…⁣

BODY | In this area of my life I want…⁣

The full moon marks the halfway point in the lunar cycle, and as the energy of the moon reaches its peak, it is a time of completion.

The energy of the moon rises in social Gemini, but we’ve got a square between Mars, the planet of war, in Sagittarius, and Saturn, the planet of discipline and karma, in Pisces. 

A square is a tense encounter between the planets involved, and the energies of the signs that they are currently in. The Moon in Gemini wants to connect and communicate, Mars in Sagittarius is a fiery explorer, and Saturn in Pisces takes feelings and emotions seriously. 

This moon could have an argumentative vibe, so try to watch your words in the next few days. If arguments arise, take a beat to reflect on the best way to resolve it. Sometimes the best reaction is no reaction at all, and when things calm down, solutions can be found in a practical way. 

Take some deep breaths with this moon. Surround yourself with people that fill your cup, and remember to pause and reflect when things become tense. Find an outlet for your emotions and come back to the issue when you’re feeling clear and centered.

Countdown To Solstice - Day 13✨

Today we breathe. One of the quickest ways to soothe the nervous system is tuning into the breath. When you are feeling overwhelmed, lost, or out of focus, tuning into the breath can bring you back into a sense of peace and calm. 

You can do breathing practices wherever you like! It only takes a few minutes to reset. Start by finding a quiet space, or going to your sacred space if possible. 

Settle in and close your eyes. Take a deep breath in through the nose, fill the lungs up with as much air as they will take. Pause at the top, and then take another sip of air, and then open the mouth and sigh it out. Make the exhale long, audible, and consciously release the breath with a sign.

Keep breathing like this for 1-2 minutes, and then return to your day!🕯️

Happy almost 2024! As the year comes to a close, what are you calling in for 2024? 

If you’re not sure yet, grab your journal and a pen, create your sacred space, and set your New Year’s intentions with a full heart and a clear mind in this 5-step process!

1.) Create a sacred space: make sure that you have a physical surrounding that inspires you and  free from distractions. Settle in with your journal and crystals, light a scented candle, diffuse essential oils, incense or anything else that resonates with you to smudge your space. 
 
2.) Go inwards: close your eyes, enter a meditative state, and ask yourself what is it that you want to manifest for 2024. Reflect on what 2023 brought you from a place of gratitude and sit with the highs and lows. 

3.) Journal: take some time to write down what you want to manifest for 2024. Maybe you have a big spiritual or emotional step you want to take in your life. Let it all out onto the pages.

4.) Commit: this is the most important step of the process. Focus on the heart of what you want to manifest. Narrow the intention down to one sentence and make it an “I am” affirmation. Write it on a piece of paper and fold it so you can keep it close. 

5.) Seal the affirmation: An affirmation is something we can use every day to reassure ourselves and can take us to a place of gratitude. Take a few breaths and sit with this energy.

From the insects and animals that help to maintain ecological balance to the less animate trees, fungi, and flowers that nurture and provide life and oxygen, all living beings are connected in one way or another.

When feeling overwhelmed, low energy, uninspired, or just a bit down, sometimes the best thing we can do is connect with nature. Here are a few rituals to consider to deepen your connection with nature, ground and center! 

1.) Hug a Tree - Trees can feel our energy and they can be incredibly healing. If you are ever feeling overwhelmed, spun out or anxious, go outside, find a tree that calls to you, and hug it until you feel it hugging you back. 

2.) Make things cozy in your home. Brew a pot of spiced tea - think ginger, chai, cinnamon, clove and settle in to enjoy it slowly. The spices in the tea will help to bring you back into your body and soothe your nervous system. 

3.) Build a Routine. Making a list to keep things organized is one of the best ways to ground yourself and calm your mind. When everything is written down in front of you, you can create order from the thoughts in your mind. 

4.) Breathe. Practice Alternate Nostril Breathing or Nadi Shodhana, using the right hand thumb to close the right nostril, inhale through the left, then use the right ring finger to close the left nostril and exhale right. Then, inhale through the right, close the right nostril, and exhale left. Repeat for as long as you like. This helps to balance the right and left sides of the brain, and bring the nervous system into a restful state.

In our natal charts, we all have a combination of the 4 elements; earth, air, fire and water. In most charts, there is a missing element, meaning that you might have a lot of planets in earth signs, but you might be missing the air element. Or you could have a lot of planets in fire signs, but be missing the element of water. 

Working with the elements in your chart, and balancing the elements that are missing, is a way to bring balance into your life incorporating your missing element in to your practices!

So if you have a lot of air, but no earth, you might need to practice grounding to stay centered. If you have a lot of fire but no water, you might need to meditate near a body of water, or incorporate baths into your weekly routine. If you have a lot of earth but no fire, you might need to practice Breath of Fire or Kapalabhati to activate and motivate you. If you have a lot of water but no earth, you might need to incorporate some movement practices to ground into the body and let emotions run through you.
